    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tools consisting of a steel pin encased in a wooden handle. These may be used by a metalworker at a lathe, for example, to press a silver or copper plate against a rotating wooden mould. Spinning mandrels have various head shapes, with which different forms can be pressed into metal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
